<br>
Folks, lets lay off Awakened Souls. I am not argueing that what they did was questionable. But lets step back and take a deep breath.<br>
<br>
Awakened Souls should have gotten the message by now. Xar, the guild leader really does not like the drama surrounding his guild on these boards and really wants to just get along with everyone. That way he and his guild can go about enjoying this game just like the rest of us.<br>
<br>
These guys in Awakened Souls have levelled pretty quick and pretty much kept to themselves. There is absolutely nothing wrong with that if thats how they want to play. But because of that they may not be completely aware of FV's social environement. They could have thought that FV was just like all the other servers and reacted accordingly.<br>
<br>
Lets wait and see what happens next time? Our guild zoned into ToV and found AS already there hunting. We exchanged some friendly shouts, a conversation broke out in, um, dutch I think (might have been german) and both guilds were there for a bit and everyone was just ducky. Instead of constantly attacking these guys, lets try encouraging them to become part of FV's community. I know Xar or someone in AS posted that they didnt want to be part of the FV community, but I think that might be because they think FV is &quot;just another blue server&quot;.<br>
<br>
Anyways, all I am really trying to say here is if we keep flaming them and /rude'ing them everytime we see them we shouldn't expect them to react any differently. If we make an effort to include them in our community and encourage them to take on the practices of similar guilds on our server then perhaps they will. <p>Kzan Verto<BR>
