<br>
Not to rain on your parade Kzan but just because Awakened Souls got along with you guys ok in Temple of Veeshan doesn't prove much to me with respect to them fitting in the EQ community.  <br>
<br>
Based on what I have seen of their actions and posts on these boards, I would disagree with your premise that they are acting this way because they feel it might just be another blue server.  Judging by their original posts introducing the guild and their actions, I would posit that a big motivating factor for them is the fact that this a relatively unspoilt server at the high-end and that they see themselves capable of being a &quot;big dog&quot; if you wil on this server.  It sounds as if many of them came to Firiona Vie for the very reason that a role-play preferred server would have less competition for them amongst powergamers.  In fact, I get the clear impression that they want to bring the &quot;blue server mentality&quot; if you will to Firiona Vie.<br>
<br>
I just see it as odd in that I keep hearing that they do not want to a part of the FV community and want to play and enjoy the game in peace.  That is fine and dandy except every player's peace and enjoyment of the game depends on the actions of other players.  If you have no disregard for other players and will use every means available to achieve something so long as it is &quot;legal&quot; under Verant's rules, you are going to step on a lot of toes.  I don't care how self-sufficient you think your guild is, if you are known as the pariah guild that is going to have repurcussions--on your interactions with other guilds (some of whom are more powerful than you) and on your recruiting in general.<br>
<br>
My final point.  Like any bully, Awakened Souls will not step on the toes of the bigger kids (in our example, Fire and Fury and Resolution) until they grow in size that they can appropriately challenge that bigger kid.  Kzan, as a member of a guild currently more powerful than Awakened Souls, you will likely a see a different side from them than members of smaller guilds will.  You mention that things seemed fine and dandy in ToV when you were both there in the same zone.  What are they going to do?  Insult you guys and get you upset at them?  Of course not.  Right now, they don't have the firepower to challenge you guys and any dispute with FnF would turn out ugly for them.<br>
<br>
Just wait a couple months.  When their ranks are swelled with more ebayers and powergamers and are able to challenge you more directly, see if they extend that same courtesy to you.  I am pretty sure that thought has come across members of both FnF and Resolution but I have no way of verifying.<br>
<br>
Sadistik Tendonslicer<br>
